# Rust Constitution

## Ownership & Borrowing (MANDATED)
- Borrow first: `&T` for read, `&mut T` for mutation, owned `T` only for transfer
- Function signatures are ownership contracts — encode move/borrow intent explicitly
- Prefer borrowed inputs (`&str`, `&[T]`) over owned `String`/`Vec<T>` when read-only
- Move at clear boundaries; cloning is a last resort, not a borrow-checker escape
- Iterator choice must match ownership semantics: `.iter()`, `.iter_mut()`, `.into_iter()`
- Never add `'static` or extra lifetimes to silence compiler diagnostics

## Error Architecture (MANDATED)
- Library/domain crates return typed errors via `thiserror`
- Application boundaries use `anyhow::Result<T>` for orchestration
- Propagate with `?`; avoid manual match ladders that only rethrow
- Add context once per boundary with `.context(...)` / `.with_context(...)`
- Recoverable business outcomes use typed results, not panic-driven control flow
- Panics are reserved for invariant violations and impossible states

## Forbidden Patterns
- `unwrap()` / `expect()` in production paths (tests and prototypes only)
- Panic-based control flow for expected, recoverable outcomes
- Repeated `.clone()` chains to bypass ownership design
- Defaulting to `Rc<RefCell<T>>` before redesigning ownership and data flow
- `unsafe` without an explicit invariant comment and a defined containment boundary
- `todo!()` / `unimplemented!()` in merged production code

## Compilation Discipline
- Fix the first compiler error first; later errors are often cascade noise
- Start with `cargo check` before running heavier gates
- Run one cargo pipeline per `target/` directory at a time
- Do not suppress lints to reach green; resolve the root cause

## Quality Gates (MINIMUM)
- `cargo check --workspace --all-targets`
- `cargo fmt --all -- --check`
- `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings`
- `cargo test --workspace`

## Escalation
- If fixes trend toward clone or refcell proliferation, stop and redesign ownership
- If compile failures cascade cross-module, resolve upstream signature contracts first

